HTML--Platform independent

Home-              How to exoplore HTML5.

Introduction-      Intro, example with explanation, web browser, page structure, History.

Editor-            Notepad.

Basics-           Document, Heading, Paragraph, Links, Images, view HTML source code of any website.

Element-          single, Nested, Empty, HTML is not case sensitive

Attribute-        Provide additional information, Specified in start tag, style, <a>--href, <img>--src,alt,height,width, <html>--lang, <h1>,<p>--title

Heading-          h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6

Paragraph-        <p>, <hr>, <br>, <pre>

Style(Attribute)-   background-color, color, font-family, font-size, text-align etc.

Formatting-         <b> = <strong>, <i> = <em>, <mark>(highlight), <small>, <del>, <ins>(underline), <sub>, <sup> etc.

Quotation-         <blockquote>, <q>(" "), <abbr>, <address>, <cite>, <bdo>.

Comments-          <!--comment-->(both single or multi-line comment).

Colors-            RGB(rr,gg,bb), HEX(#rrggbb), HSL(hue,saturation,lightness), RGBA, HSLA.

CSS-             3 ways:
                        Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements.(<h1 style="color:blue;">A Blue Heading</h1>)
                        Internal - by using a <style> element in the <head> section.
                                   <head>
                                        <style>
                                               body {background-color: powderblue;}
                                               h1   {color: blue;}
                                               p    {color: red;}
                                         </style>
                                   </head>
                       External - by using a <link> element to link to an external CSS file.
                              "styles.css":
                                           body {
                                                 background-color: powderblue;
                                                }
                                             h1 {
                                                 color: blue;
                                                }
                                              p {
                                                 color: red;
                                                }
                Border, Padding, Margin.

Links-         Hyperlinks(<a>), target attribute(self, blank, parent, top), URLs(Absolute, Relative), <a href="web link"><img src="pic"></a>, Email send, Button, Title(abbr), Link Color, Button Color, Link Bookmark.

Images-        Attributes(src, alt,height,width), Style, animated images, image as link(<a><img></a>), float(style), Image formate, Image Map, Background image, Picture element

Favicon-       create self fevicon, Syntax.

Page title-    Syntax.

Tables-        Syntax, td, tr, th, caption, colgroup, col, thead, tbody, tfoot.
Table Border-  double border, single border, background color, round table border(Double or single), different border styles, border color.
Table size-    width(Table or colomn), height(row).
Table header-  set header, align, for multiple column(colspan), caption.
Padding & spacing-   padding(th,td), border spacing.
Rowspan & Colspan-
Table styling-  zebra stripes, Horizontal dividers, hover, colgroup(empty), Hide columns.
Table Colgroup-  syntax, CSS,  Hide columns.

Lists-          unordered(ul),  ordered(ol), Description(dl>dt>dd).
unordered lists-  nested list, Horizontal List with CSS(float:left)
ordered lists-    The Type Attribute(1,A,a,I,i), Control List Counting(<ol start="50">), Nested Lists.
Description Lists-  syntax.

Block & Inline-   Block-level Elements(always starts on a new line)(<p>,<div>,etc), Inline Elements( not start on a new line)(<span>,etc)

                                An inline element cannot contain a block-level element!

Div-              Center align a <div>--margin:auto; positioning and formatting content and allow elements float next to each other--float:left; displayed side by side --display: inline-block;  display:flex; display: grid;---grid-template-columns: 33% 33% 33%;

Classess(.)-       syntax, case sensitive, Multiple Classes, Multiple HTML elements can share the same class,  It can also be used by a JavaScript to access and manipulate elements(Hide element program of JS).

Id(#)-            case sensitive,Bookmarks with ID, used to specify a unique id for an HTML element, You cannot have more than one element with the same id, used by JavaScript to access and manipulate the element(program to change text).

iframe-           used to display a web page within a web page, Syntax, style,height and width attributes, Remove the default Border(style="border:none;"), Target for a Link.

JavaScript-       Defines a client-side script, Program to display date and time, <script> Tag(Hello program), JavaScript can change styles, JavaScript can change attributes(Program to on off bulb), noscript.

File Path-        Paths to insert a image, Absolute File Paths(complete url), Relative File Paths(folder location).
